codex
The patch adds important erasure functionality, but the new provenance doctor misclassifies a known unerasable edge shape, and source erasure can time out when vector projection work is pending. These are actionable correctness issues in the new/changed behavior.

Full review comments:

- [P2] Count NULL-source edges as unerasable — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s5/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:6756-6761
  When a `canonical_edges` row has `source_id IS NULL` but a non-NULL `logical_id`, this query adds it to `governed` and the later `unerasable_rows` calculation subtracts it as purge-addressable. Edges are not purged by their own `logical_id` (purge only resolves nodes and then deletes touching edges), so `doctor orphan-provenance` can exit clean while the exact legacy/corrupt edge shape called out by the migration comments is still unreachable by any erasure verb.

- [P2] Drain unqueued projection work before freezing — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s5/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:6652-6653
  For `erase_source`/`excise_source` called right after writing a vector-indexed row, freezing before the first `drain` can strand work that has not yet been queued: `wait_for_idle` sees pending DB work, but the frozen dispatcher cannot scan and enqueue it, so the erasure waits for the full lifecycle timeout and returns `Scheduler`. `purge` already does an unfrozen drain before freezing for this reason; the shared source erasure path needs the same ordering.
